text: What is this “cheese and biscuits” circuit? How have I missed this?! I love cheese.
author: vincentmoss

text: Owen, first tweet about this terrible front page is right. Follow up labelling all MSM as homogeneous is wrong - but you know that.
author: vincentmoss

text: Search me. If it got clicks, almost definitely, I suspect. But on the Clangers’ knobbly planet somewhere near Planet Lala, Major Clanger would  be telling the family he has had a “very good day”.
author: vincentmoss

text: Get it up fast. Get the clicks. Say we made a mistake. Take it down (slowly). Fooling no one. (Deputy) heads won’t roll.
author: vincentmoss

text: John is right. Of course, the story must be covered. It’s how you do it. Media orgs have a responsibility to their readers and the wider public.
author: vincentmoss

text: It’s how you do it. Tone, writing, video use. Judgement.  We all know what went on today with elements of online etc.  It’s like the Wild West of 80s print.
author: vincentmoss

text: These issues are a judgement call. Terrible judgement. Appalling insensitivity to the victims.  Thoughts with all those affected by this atrocity and my friends in NZ.
author: vincentmoss
